pageInfo.description: The Official Source of Times Square NYC

items.text: This area was originally named Longacre Square but was renamed in 1904 when the NY Times moved to the skyscraper now known as One Times Square at 42nd St., famous for the Times Square Ball drop.
When the New York Times moved into offices at Broadway and 42nd Street on Dec 31, 1904, it threw a party so legendary that New Yorkers started to celebrate New Year’s Eve in Times Square every year.
Don't forget to stop by the Visitor Center!
Ziyaretçilerini büyüleyen, ışıltılı ve şık otellerin, restoranların bulunduğu dünyanın en ünlü, en canlı meydanlarından! Civardaki ünlü tiyatrolarda müzikali ya da tiyatro oyununu izlemelisiniz! :)

tip.text: Most crowded NYC attraction, be prepared for slow walkers! Billboard lights are always illuminated and awesome to see at night. Easily accessible by subway or walking. Lots of good eats on 9th Avenue
